Continue from the previous zDash implementation.

Project:

⬡ zDash · FULL SYSTEM BLUEPRINT v2.0

Now execute ONLY:

PHASE 16 · SOVEREIGN ENTERPRISE GRID + ON-PREM APPLIANCE + GLOBAL EXPANSION CONTROL PLANE
Multi-Region Control Plane + On-Prem Appliance + Edge Runners + Data Residency Enforcement + Global Partner Operations

Do not rebuild Phase 1–15 from scratch.
Extend the existing codebase cleanly.

Assume these phases already exist:

PHASE 1–15:
- Janie Server
- Agent Runtime
- XAU Scanner
- Guardian Risk System
- Scheduler / IoT dry-run automation
- Backtesting Lab
- Content Pipeline
- React Dashboard
- Auth / RBAC / Audit
- Multi-tenant SaaS
- Workers / Realtime / Alerts
- Billing / Marketplace / Enterprise Packaging
- AI Ops / Governance / Compliance
- Ops Autopilot / Incident / SLA / Integrations
- Mobile App / Partner API / SDKs / Sandbox
- Tauri Desktop / Distribution / Public Launch
- GA Readiness / Marketplace V2 / Partner Program / Product Analytics / LegalOps

============================================================
PHASE 16 OBJECTIVE
============================================================

Build the sovereign enterprise and global expansion layer for zDash.

Main goals:

1. Add multi-region control plane model
2. Add region-aware tenant routing
3. Add data residency enforcement engine
4. Add sovereign deployment profile system
5. Add on-prem appliance packaging model
6. Add edge runner registration and heartbeat
7. Add edge job dispatch and result collection
8. Add offline-first enterprise sync model
9. Add customer-managed key shell
10. Add BYOK/KMS adapter interface
11. Add enterprise policy bundle export
12. Add partner reseller operations workflow
13. Add regional marketplace governance
14. Add regional billing / tax metadata shell
15. Add global support escalation matrix
16. Add enterprise account hierarchy
17. Add cross-region observability summary
18. Add global rollout planner
19. Add sovereign compliance dashboard
20. Add final Phase 16 tests, docs, runbooks, and acceptance checklist

IMPORTANT SAFETY RULES:
- Do not enable live trading by default.
- Do not enable real IoT actions by default.
- Do not enable real social posting by default.
- Do not bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Do not bypass content approval checks.
- Do not bypass tenant isolation.
- Do not bypass billing entitlements.
- Do not bypass governance policies.
- Do not bypass final GA safety gates.
- Data residency policies must fail closed when enforcement is enabled.
- Edge runners must default to dry-run/simulation mode.
- On-prem appliance must not embed secrets.
- Customer-managed key integration must be shell/mock by default.
- No raw keys, secrets, broker credentials, signing keys, cloud credentials, API keys, or tokens may be logged, exported, synced, or displayed.
- Cross-region sync must never move tenant data to a forbidden region.
- Offline sync must be redacted and conflict-safe.
- Reseller and partner workflows must not bypass tenant ownership or billing authority.

